svg.title: Insights
svg.text: The identity/position of Abby has a serious impact on the interaction between users and Abby.
The right timing is a major part for a decent interaction especially for conversations.
Abby needs to leverage different mental model and expectation from beginner users to expert ones.
Abby should follow basic social and culture norms to make natural interactions.
Abby will be silent unless summoned
When guests prefer to type than speak
Abby inherits info from the host instantly
Abby learns user’s preferences throughout time
Abby will live up the atomosphere when nobody talks
Abby provides intuitive instructions for beginner users
Abby’s introduction is triggered by guest’s first coming into the house
Abby’s time check is triggered by certain time prior to check-in time
Abby’s will always be triggered by hearing “Abby”
A sudden voice might scare users
